"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(*)\nFROM member\nJOIN major ON member.link_to_major = major.major_id\nWHERE major.major_name LIKE '%Education%'\nAND major.college = 'College of Education & Human Services';\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of members who have a major related to \"Education\" in the \"College of Education & Human Services.\" It uses a JOIN to connect the `member` table with the `major` table based on the foreign key relationship, and it filters the results based on the major name and college."